  "commentary": "With SPX at 7107 sitting just below the GEX flip at 7109, dealers are positioned as net gamma sellers here, creating a pocket of instability right at current levels. The massive -18045M negative gamma wall at 7110 means any move above will force dealers to chase momentum higher, while the strong positive gamma walls at 7100 (+5809M) and 7150 (+5864M) should provide meaningful support and resistance respectively. The recent GEX surge combined with the PIN regime suggests dealers will aggressively fade any move toward 7200 (max positive gamma) but could get caught in momentum flows if we break above 7110.\n\nKey levels: 7110 breakout trigger, 7100 support, 7150/7200 resistance zones.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile chop between 7100-7150 with potential for sharp moves if 7110 breaks.",
